isNameLegal

public static boolean isNameLegal(String name)
judge whether the document name is legal. Naming rules: 1.The name of the key is a sequence of Unicode characters, whose maximum length of the UTF-8 encoding is 1024 bytes. 2 The name of the key should be used "/" separated by the full name of the path: such as "ucsm/bin/ucsm.exe" 3.Recommend character are letter and number: [0-9a-zA-Z], special characters:!,-,_,.,*,',(,)

Parameters:
name: - document name
Returns:
boolean: weather the document name is legal
